<chapter subject="Biology" id="301" name="The Living World">
    <easy>
        <question>
            <text>Increase in mass and increase in number of individuals are twin characteristics of ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Growth</option><option id="B">Reproduction</option><option id="C">Metabolism</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>In multi-cellular organisms, growth takes place by cell division.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Defining property of living organisms is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Consciousness</option><option id="B">Growth</option><option id="C">Reproduction</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Response to external stimuli is found in all living beings.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Sum total of all chemical reactions occurring in our body is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Metabolism</option><option id="B">Anabolism</option><option id="C">Catabolism</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Includes constructive and destructive processes.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>In plants, growth by cell division occurs ____ throughout their life span.</text>
            <option id="A">Continuously</option><option id="B">Only up to certain age</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Due to presence of meristematic tissues.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>System of providing distinct and proper names to organisms is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Nomenclature</option><option id="B">Identification</option><option id="C">Classification</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>So they are known by same name all over world.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Scientific name of Mango is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Mangifera indica</option><option id="B">Solanum tuberosum</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Mangifera denotes Genus and indica denotes Species.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>ICBN stands for International Code for ____ Nomenclature.</text>
            <option id="A">Botanical</option><option id="B">Biological</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Sets rules for naming plants.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>ICZN stands for International Code for ____ Nomenclature.</text>
            <option id="A">Zoological</option><option id="B">Biological</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Sets rules for naming animals.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Binomial nomenclature was given by ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Carolus Linnaeus</option><option id="B">Aristotle</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>In his book Systema Naturae.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>In binomial name, the first word denotes ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Genus</option><option id="B">Species</option><option id="C">Order</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Also called generic name.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>In binomial name, the second word denotes ____ epithet.</text>
            <option id="A">Specific</option><option id="B">Generic</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Identifies the individual species.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Process by which anything is grouped into categories based on observable characters is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Classification</option><option id="B">Identification</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Simplifies study of biodiversity.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Scientific term for categories in classification is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Taxa</option><option id="B">Species</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Singular: Taxon.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Study of identification, nomenclature and classification of organisms is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Taxonomy</option><option id="B">Ecology</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Greek: taxis = arrangement, nomos = law.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Branch of study that deals with evolutionary relationships between organisms is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Systematics</option><option id="B">Taxonomy</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Latin: systema = systematic arrangement.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Basic unit of classification is ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Species</option><option id="B">Kingdom</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Group of individuals with fundamental similarities.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Group of related species is called ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Genus</option><option id="B">Family</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Example: Panthera leo, P. pardus, P. tigris.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Group of related genera is called ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Family</option><option id="B">Order</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Example: Felidae includes Panthera and Felis.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Related families are kept under a/an ____.</text>
            <option id="A">Order</option><option id="B">Class</option><option id="C">phi</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Example: Carnivora includes Felidae and Canidae.</explanation></question>
        <question>
